text: Casey Murdock is an American politician and a Republican member of the Oklahoma House of Representatives representing District 61 since 2014. He is running in a special election for the Oklahoma Senate seat vacated by Bryce Marlatt. Murdock studied agricultural business at the Oklahoma Panhandle State University, where he graduated in 1992. He was first elected to the Oklahoma House of Representatives in 2014.
